'I would have liked it if Falcao was with [former Man Utd manager] Sir Alex Ferguson,' Mendes told La Sexta.

'He is a player who needs to play 90 minutes and I don't understand [why he isn't].'

Mendes has previously clashed with the former Holland manager, insisting Falcao will play 'for one of the best teams in the world, if it's United or not,' after he was left out of the squad for a 1-0 defeat to Southampton.

